\begin_layout Section
Conclusions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The investigation of self-cosistent QM combination with RISM model reveals
 that for neutral solutes, the accuracy of the calculated solvation free
 energy is mainly determined by the solute cavity formation.
 The better agreement with experimental results could be obtained by applying
 partial molar volume correction as reported also in previous non-SCF studies.
 Another important factor, the change of the solute electrostatic property,
 which is perturbed by the solvent medium, is also found to have noticeable
 contribution to the solvation free energy calculation.
 Meanwhile, from the RDF in SCF-RISM, we found that the rearrangement of
 the solute charge density calculation causes the strengthening of the hydrogen
 bond between solute and water solvent.
